   News that stays news
   I just came across a wonderful definition of literature from Ezra
   Pound: "News that stays news."  It was quoted by Paul Fussell in Samuel
   Johnson and the Life of Writing to characterize how Johnson transformed
   his career as a hack writer on London's Grub Street into something much
   more.  I love it!  Literature is "News that stays news." That is a
   definition to conjure with!﻿
